# Flutter Material Design Standards

## Context

- Apply when creating or modifying UI components in Flutter
- Ensures consistent Material Design implementation
- Maintains visual harmony across the application
- Follows Google's Material Design 3 specifications

## Critical Rules

### Material Components
- Use Material 3 widgets over basic Flutter widgets:
  - Prefer `ElevatedButton` over `RawMaterialButton`
  - Use `Card` for contained content blocks
  - Implement `AppBar` for consistent navigation
  - Use `BottomNavigationBar` for primary navigation
- Apply Material theming through `ThemeData`
- Use `MaterialApp` as the root widget

### Design System
- Follow Material Design elevation system:
  - 0-5 for cards and surfaces
  - 1-3 for buttons and FABs
  - 2-4 for navigation drawers
- Implement consistent spacing using Material's 8dp grid:
  - Base spacing unit: 8.0
  - Content padding: 16.0
  - Section spacing: 24.0
- Use Material color system:
  - Define primary, secondary, and tertiary colors
  - Include light/dark variants
  - Implement proper contrast ratios

### Typography
- Use Material type scale:
  - Display: Large, Medium, Small
  - Headline: Large, Medium, Small
  - Title: Large, Medium, Small
  - Label: Large, Medium, Small
  - Body: Large, Medium, Small
- Maintain consistent text styles through `TextTheme`

### Component Guidelines
- Follow Material motion patterns for animations
- Implement proper touch targets (minimum 48x48dp)
- Use standard iconography from `Icons` class
- Maintain consistent corner radius across components
- Apply proper state layers (pressed, hovered, focused)

## Examples

<example>
// Good Implementation - Proper Material Design Usage
class ProductCard extends StatelessWidget {
  final Product product;

  const ProductCard({required this.product, super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Card(
      elevation: 2,
      margin: const EdgeInsets.all(8.0),
      child: Padding(
        padding: const EdgeInsets.all(16.0),
        child: Column(
          crossAxisAlignment: CrossAxisAlignment.start,
          children: [
            Text(
              product.name,
              style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.titleLarge,
            ),
            const SizedBox(height: 8.0),
            Text(
              product.description,
              style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyMedium,
            ),
            const SizedBox(height: 16.0),
            ElevatedButton(
              onPressed: () => _handlePurchase(),
              child: const Text('Buy Now'),
            ),
          ],
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
</example>

